  }
  for p := range seen {
      for _, m := range reg.ModelsByProvider(p) {
          ...
      }
  }

The outer loop 'for p := range seen' iterates over a map in nondeterministic order. Go's map iteration order is randomized per run (by design). This does not affect correctness of the individual assertion (each p is checked independently), but it makes test output ordering nondeterministic and slightly harder to diagnose when failures occur.

## Severity rationale

Not a correctness bug — the assertion is still valid. But a slice sorted by provider string would be both deterministic and easier to read in failure output. Minor nit.

## Fix suggestion

Convert to sorted slice:
  providers := make([]provenance.Provider, 0, len(seen))
  for p := range seen { providers = append(providers, p) }
  sort.Slice(providers, func(i, j int) bool { return string(providers[i]) < string(providers[j]) })
  for _, p := range providers { ... }

