## Engineering Tradeoffs

| Decision | Options | Chosen | Rationale |
|----------|---------|--------|-----------|
| Type structure | Separate Canonical + ModelRef vs flat ModelRef with formatters | Flat ModelRef | Reviewer C-B1: Canonical duplicated ModelRef fields. Drop the wrapper. |
| Format dispatch | Sibling String methods vs typed scheme enum | CanonicalScheme enum + Format method | Reviewer C-B2: idiomatic Go uses typed dispatch. Modality is the precedent. |
| Decomposition timing | Eager in Ref() vs baked into static gen vs lazy | Baked into static gen | Reviewer C-I2: zero runtime cost for the common case. Runtime decomp only for unknown user input via Resolve. |
| Override storage | Hand-edited Go map vs JSON file vs inline | JSON in testdata/ | Reviewer C-I3: single source consumed by codegen + runtime tests. Easier to audit/diff. |
| Resolve return | (ModelRef, error) vs ([]ModelRef, error) | []ModelRef + ErrAmbiguous | Reviewer A-B4 + B-F1: inputs like "claude" inherently match multiple. Be explicit. |
| Scheme detection | Always require --scheme vs auto-detect with override | Auto-detect with --scheme override | Best UX. Detect by prefix (pkg:, /), fall back to raw, error if ambiguous. |
| Suffix table source | Hardcoded Go vs same JSON as overrides | Same JSON file | Audit and edit in one place. |
| Versioned variants | Mixed into suffix table vs separate rule | Separate rule (regex on dotted version) | Reviewer A-B2: suffix matching can't handle k2.5/v2.5 patterns. |
| Schema version | 0.1.0 vs 0.0.2 | 0.0.2 | User correction: additive changes, patch bump. |

